  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mold Design Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze product designs for manufacturability and cost efficiency (DFM).</li><li>Develop 3D/2D tool designs using AutoCAD and SolidWorks for plastic injection molding.</li><li>Create mold design layouts, lead design reviews, and ensure accuracy.</li><li>Design precision molds meeting product specs and production standards.</li><li>Manage mold projects, coordinate with teams and customers.</li><li>Prepare bills of materials, maintain documentation for traceability.</li><li>Participate in First-Off Tool reviews and evaluate tool readiness.</li><li>Analyze tooling issues, identify root causes, and implement solutions.</li><li>Develop complex mold designs for production release.</li><li>Apply knowledge of plastics and elastomers for informed design decisions.</li><li>Utilize 3D modeling and GD&T expertise for design precision.</li><li>Communicate effectively with stakeholders, collaborate as a team player.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Proficiency in SolidWorks, AutoCAD, and GD&T.</li><li>Knowledge of plastic injection molding and automotive industry standards.</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and teamwork mindset.</li><li>5 days' work week.</li></ul>",
